1
00:00:02,486 --> 00:00:03,980
<i>- Previously on</i> The Resident...
- You're fired.

2
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:05,887
You're afraid of me.

3
00:00:05,923 --> 00:00:07,005
<i>And you should be.</i>

4
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:08,401
<i>Security will escort you out.</i>

5
00:00:08,425 --> 00:00:10,626
<i>If my sister has a child,</i>

6
00:00:10,661 --> 00:00:12,138
then that child
becomes my family, too.

7
00:00:12,162 --> 00:00:13,857
Are you saying you'll
be my baby's godmother?

8
00:00:13,881 --> 00:00:14,863
<i>You said yes?</i>

9
00:00:14,898 --> 00:00:16,298
All right, so what's your plan

10
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:17,427
if Adaku's baby becomes
your responsibility?

11
00:00:17,451 --> 00:00:19,251
I don't have one.

12
00:00:19,286 --> 00:00:22,821
<i>There was a learning
curve, but I mastered it.</i>

13
00:00:22,857 --> 00:00:24,401
Why don't you come
over to our place later?

14
00:00:24,425 --> 00:00:26,191
Uh, not tonight.

15
00:00:26,227 --> 00:00:27,526
<i>I'm tired.</i>

16
00:00:27,561 --> 00:00:30,011
<i>A little time alone
with my thoughts.</i>

17
00:00:36,787 --> 00:00:39,683
<i>This incredible woman
had the ability to save a life</i>

18
00:00:39,707 --> 00:00:41,767
<i>right in front of me. And
I knew, in that moment,</i>

19
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:43,408
<i>that I wanted to be a person</i>

20
00:00:43,443 --> 00:00:46,945
<i>who could jump out of
the car to help people.</i>

21
00:00:46,981 --> 00:00:48,980
<i>So that's what I do.</i>

22
00:01:01,211 --> 00:01:03,790
Methodist Memorial
went with someone else.

23
00:01:03,814 --> 00:01:07,949
Apparently they checked
in with my last employer.

24
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:09,779
Red Rock has
gotten you blacklisted

25
00:01:09,803 --> 00:01:10,914
from every hospital in Atlanta.

26
00:01:10,938 --> 00:01:12,138
I want to practice medicine,

27
00:01:12,172 --> 00:01:14,639
I'll have to find
work out of town.

28
00:01:16,259 --> 00:01:17,904
Have a long-distance
relationship

29
00:01:17,928 --> 00:01:20,779
or give up being a doctor.
This is what it's come to?

30
00:01:20,814 --> 00:01:21,947
No, it hasn't.

31
00:01:21,982 --> 00:01:24,616
We're gonna figure this out.

32
00:01:24,651 --> 00:01:26,162
You should go,
you're gonna be late.

33
00:01:26,186 --> 00:01:27,769
Eh...

34
00:01:31,492 --> 00:01:33,486
You have any idea why
Reggie wanted to see you?

35
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:35,627
No, he just said to meet him

36
00:01:35,663 --> 00:01:37,629
at the Georgia
FC practice field.

37
00:01:37,665 --> 00:01:40,299
Is it bad that I had no idea
Atlanta has a soccer team?

38
00:01:41,318 --> 00:01:42,800
Yes.

39
00:01:42,836 --> 00:01:44,503
But I forgive you.

40
00:01:52,429 --> 00:01:55,447
Well, hel-hello, good sir.

41
00:01:55,482 --> 00:01:56,815
Some tea and crumpets, perhaps?

42
00:01:56,851 --> 00:01:58,950
Ha. Very funny.

43
00:01:58,986 --> 00:02:01,014
I need to make a good
impression on my new attending.

44
00:02:01,038 --> 00:02:04,490
Ah, right, first day in the
dual residency program.

45
00:02:04,525 --> 00:02:05,768
Internal medicine
this week. ER next.

46
00:02:05,792 --> 00:02:07,192
And then I go back and forth.

47
00:02:07,227 --> 00:02:10,996
A foot in two departments
fundamentally at odds.

48
00:02:11,031 --> 00:02:13,309
Well, as a dual resident, I
can reach across the aisle,

49
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:16,112
- help each department
see how the other lives.
- If you say so.

50
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:18,036
But lose the bow tie.

51
00:02:18,071 --> 00:02:19,682
You look like a
chemistry professor

52
00:02:19,706 --> 00:02:21,039
who refuses to hand out As

53
00:02:21,074 --> 00:02:23,358
even when they're
totally deserved.

54
00:02:23,393 --> 00:02:25,793
- That was oddly specific.
- I was really good at chemistry.

55
00:02:29,683 --> 00:02:31,967
Fine. You know what?

56
00:02:32,002 --> 00:02:33,502
Okay, baby girl.

57
00:02:33,537 --> 00:02:35,703
Your bottle is coming right up.

58
