<i>All through the town.</i> ♪

68
00:03:11,725 --> 00:03:13,709
- Reggie.
- Dax.

69
00:03:13,744 --> 00:03:15,910
- What's good, Conrad?
- Yeah, good to see you.

70
00:03:15,946 --> 00:03:17,423
- Good to see you.
- Good to see you.

71
00:03:17,447 --> 00:03:20,065
I want you to meet my
mentee, Dax Ramsey.

72
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:22,050
Yeah, rookie out of Memphis.

73
00:03:22,085 --> 00:03:24,948
- You're supposed to be
the next face of the franchise.
- Yeah. That's the plan.

74
00:03:24,972 --> 00:03:26,583
If I can get my
injuries under control.

75
00:03:26,607 --> 00:03:28,451
Today is Dax's
first practice back.

76
00:03:28,475 --> 00:03:31,577
- He's recovering from
a calf injury.
- Which feels fine, but...

77
00:03:31,612 --> 00:03:33,456
what worries me is I get
these cramps and injuries

78
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:34,762
from the smallest things.

79
00:03:34,798 --> 00:03:37,115
The more conditioning I
do, the weaker I seem to get.

80
00:03:37,151 --> 00:03:39,418
The team doc, he
ran a bunch of tests.

81
00:03:39,453 --> 00:03:41,953
Everything came back normal,
so he cleared Dax to play.

82
00:03:41,988 --> 00:03:44,050
But I keep telling him
there's something up with me.

83
00:03:44,074 --> 00:03:45,718
But he won't listen,
so I asked Reggie

84
00:03:45,742 --> 00:03:47,454
if he knew a doctor who
could give me a second opinion.

85
00:03:47,478 --> 00:03:48,627
And I thought,

86
00:03:48,662 --> 00:03:51,062
why not the guy who
saved my life in zero G?

87
00:03:53,249 --> 00:03:55,194
Yeah, well, I'm happy to take
a look at your medical records.

88
00:03:55,218 --> 00:03:58,186
That's me. Good looking out.

89
00:03:58,222 --> 00:04:00,238
I'll let you know
if I find anything.

90
00:04:02,509 --> 00:04:03,591
Buckle up.

91
00:04:03,644 --> 00:04:04,821
This may just be
a practice game,

92
00:04:04,845 --> 00:04:08,430
but these boys are
about to put on a show.

93
00:04:08,465 --> 00:04:11,299
Ball. Box.

94
00:04:12,469 --> 00:04:15,370
♪ <i>La, la, la, la, la, la</i> ♪

95
00:04:15,405 --> 00:04:17,155
♪ <i>La, la, la, la, la, la, la</i> ♪

96
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:20,224
♪ <i>La, la, la, la, la, la</i> ♪

97
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:21,837
♪ <i>Nah-nah-nah-nah-nah-nah-nah,
hey!</i> ♪

98
00:04:21,861 --> 00:04:24,629
♪ <i>La, la, la, la, la, la</i> ♪

99
00:04:24,664 --> 00:04:27,615
♪ <i>La, la, la,
la, la, la, la...</i> ♪

100
00:04:27,650 --> 00:04:29,301
His footwork's insane.

101
00:04:29,336 --> 00:04:31,870
That's why Dax is the best
rookie this team's ever had.

102
00:04:39,212 --> 00:04:40,294
I need help.

103
00:04:45,486 --> 00:04:48,470
All right, I got you, I got you.

104
00:04:50,674 --> 00:04:52,523
- Oh! Aah!
- All right.

105
00:04:52,559 --> 00:04:54,537
Your ribs are fractured
in several places.

106
00:04:54,561 --> 00:04:56,445
Your chest wall is unstable.

107
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:59,865
- We need to get Dax
to a hospital. I'll call 911.

108
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:01,983
♪ ♪

109
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:14,512
Hang in there.

110
00:05:15,915 --> 00:05:17,265
Trauma Bay 10.

111
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:19,211
When the paramedics
called this in,

112
00:05:19,235 --> 00:05:20,563
I wouldn't have guessed
you were with them.

113
00:05:20,587 --> 00:05:22,198
Yeah, trust me, I didn't
expect to be here either.

114
00:05:22,222 --> 00:05:23,883
- Who's the trauma surgeon
on today?
- Bell.

115
00:05:23,907 --> 00:05:26,441
- He's already on his way.
- Correction. He's already here.

116
00:05:26,476 --> 00:05:28,504
Hawkins, you care to explain
how you ended up here,

117
00:05:28,528 --> 00:05:29,895
yet again, with a patient?

118
00:05:29,930 --> 00:05:31,908
I was at the practice
center when Dax got injured.

119
00:05:31,932 --> 00:05:33,576
- All right, what do we have?
- 19-year-old male,

120
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,850
blunt trauma to the
chest and abdomen.

121
00:05:35,903 --> 00:05:38,003
Hypotensive and
tachycardic en route.

122
00:05:39,239 --> 00:05:40,516
I'm Dr. Feldman,
this is Dr. Bell.

123
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:42,157
Do you have any allergies

124
00:05:42,192 --> 00:05:43,402
to any medications
we should know about?

125
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:44,626
Not that I know of.

126
00:05:44,661 --> 00:05:46,356
Nice as it is to
see you, Conrad,

127
00:05:46,380 --> 00:05:48,658
- Logan Kim isn't going to like
that you're here.
- I know.

128
00:05:48,682 --> 00:05:51,983
- I can't just leave him
while he's still in pain.
- Hey, Conrad?

129
00:05:52,019 --> 00:05:54,169
Yeah, I'm here. We're
gonna take care of you.

130
00:05:54,204 --> 00:05:55,554
I'm a friend of the patient,

131
00:05:55,589 --> 00:05:58,006
that's not against
hospital policy.

132
00:06:00,728 --> 00:06:03,512
Okay, his O2 stats are
dropping. We need to intubate him.

133
00:06:05,632 --> 00:06:07,992
- Chest cavity is full of blood.
- Get me a chest tube kit.

134
00:06:09,019 --> 00:06:10,396
Now, as the friend
of the patient,

135
00:06:10,420 --> 00:06:12,565
I'm gonna have to ask you to
step outside the trauma bay.

136
00:06:12,589 --> 00:06:14,066
- That is hospital policy.
- I understand.

137
00:06:14,090 --> 00:06:16,290
I'm playing by the
rules on this one.

138
00:06:24,284 --> 00:06:27,101
<i>Dr. Lee to Infectious Disease.</i>

139
00:06:31,058 --> 00:06:32,435
Hey, Dad. I was
just on my way out.

140
00:06:32,459 --> 00:06:33,739
Where are you? I'll pick you up.

141
00:06:35,896 --> 00:06:37,295
You're where?

142
00:06:42,969 --> 00:06:44,553
It's fine. I'm fine.

143
00:06:44,588 --> 00:06:46,399
You're not fine.
You got arrested.

144
00:06:46,423 --> 00:06:48,273
You see any handcuffs? I'm okay.

145
00:06:48,308 --> 00:06:51,076
Can we just please go?

146
00:06:51,111 --> 00:06:53,477
What the hell happened?
You got into a fight?

147
00:06:53,513 --> 00:06:55,964
- It was schoolyard stuff.
- Between two grown men?

148
00:06:55,999 --> 00:06:57,782
Well, he threw the first punch.

149
00:06:57,818 --> 00:06:59,962
The police agree that I'm
innocent, so they released me.

150
00:06:59,986 --> 00:07:02,887
- Who were you fighting?
- This guy, he bought my car.

151
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:05,439
He had buyer's remorse,
he thought I'd take it back.

152
00:07:05,475 --> 00:07:08,109
- And then he made fun of my hat.
- Wait, you-you sold your car?

153
00:07:08,144 --> 00:07:10,428
You've had that
car for 20 years.

154
00:07:10,463 --> 00:07:12,246
Nic, nothing lasts forever.

155
00:07:12,282 --> 00:07:13,248
Dad.

156
00:07:13,283 --> 00:07:17,051
I'm worried about you.

157
00:07:17,086 --> 00:07:20,738
Yes, look... Okay, I've
been a-a little down lately.

158
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:23,574
But who doesn't hit a rough
patch every now and then?

159
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:25,844
I'm fine.

160
00:07:25,879 --> 00:07:27,662
I promise.

161
00:07:33,654 --> 00:07:36,165
Well, the repeat
cultures are negative.

162
00:07:36,189 --> 00:07:37,906
Plus no fever in two days.

163
00:07:37,941 --> 00:07:40,659
Which means your
infection is clearing.

164
00:07:40,694 --> 00:07:43,578
So I finally get
to hold my baby?

165
00:07:43,613 --> 00:07:44,862
Yes, indeed.

166
00:07:44,898 --> 00:07:48,849
However, the results
happen to be so good that...

167
00:07:48,885 --> 00:07:52,186
We can discharge you and send
you home with oral antibiotics.

168
00:07:52,221 --> 00:07:53,205
Yes!

169
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,288
Ah...

170
00:07:54,323 --> 00:07:57,876
Thank you both so
much for everything.

171
00:07:57,911 --> 00:08:00,489
- You got it.
- I can't wait to have
Michelle in my arms

172
00:08:00,513 --> 00:08:02,593
- and finally to be able
to get out of here.
- Mm-hmm.

173
00:08:04,667 --> 00:08:07,118
Do you think she'll
know who I am?

174
00:08:07,154 --> 00:08:09,771
I'm sure she'll know

175
00:08:09,806 --> 00:08:11,956
by the love you give her.

176
00:08:14,828 --> 00:08:17,279
- Look at how cute she is.
- Yeah.

177
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:21,065
As my admitting resident,

178
00:08:21,101 --> 00:08:23,301
you are gatekeeper
to the medicine floor.

179
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:24,636
And when I say "gatekeeper,"

180
00:08:24,671 --> 00:08:26,649
I mean you are to be
a blocking machine.

181
00:08:26,673 --> 00:08:29,791
Mrs. Allen, 68-year-old female
with alcoholic pancreatitis.

182
00:08:29,826 --> 00:08:32,076
Know what went wrong here?

183
00:08:32,112 --> 00:08:34,090
She binged on alcohol and
gave herself pancreatitis?

184
00:08:34,114 --> 00:08:36,547
Wrong. The ER were too
slow giving her a benzo,

185
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:38,561
so now we're stuck chasing
her withdrawal symptoms.

186
00:08:38,585 --> 00:08:40,752
That's not entirely
fair. The ER is always...

187
00:08:40,787 --> 00:08:42,736
Mr. Hopper, 80-year-old man.

188
00:08:42,772 --> 00:08:44,806
Fell in his home,
sprained his hip.

189
00:08:44,841 --> 00:08:45,985
Care to guess the mistake?

190
00:08:46,009 --> 00:08:48,376
He's an elderly
man who lives alone

191
00:08:48,412 --> 00:08:50,773
- and he needs
discharge planning.
- Which could have been done

192
00:08:50,797 --> 00:08:53,565
while he was waiting in the
ER. Instead, he's taking up

193
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,227
one of our beds,
waiting for a placement.

194
00:08:55,251 --> 00:08:57,211
I could go on, but
the trend is clear.

195
00:08:57,236 --> 00:09:00,572
We're accepting patients from
the ER that don't belong here.

196
00:09:00,607 --> 00:09:03,275
Look, I agree
that these patients

197
00:09:03,310 --> 00:09:04,954
in particular could have
been managed better,

198
00:09:04,978 --> 00:09:08,062
but most of the patients on
this floor do need to be here.

199
00:09:11,702 --> 00:09:15,286
I know you're not a
pure medicine resident,

200
00:09:15,321 --> 00:09:18,189
that you've been tainted by
habits you learned in the ER.

201
00:09:18,225 --> 00:09:22,360
- I wouldn't say that...
- But you're on this team now.

202
00:09:22,396 --> 00:09:24,328
So, what are you going to be?

203
00:09:26,149 --> 00:09:27,615
A blocking machine.

204
00:09:27,650 --> 00:09:31,252
A blocking... machine.

205
00:09:37,894 --> 00:09:39,644
Dr. Hawkins...

206
00:09:39,679 --> 00:09:43,314
this is Bill Landry,
owner of Georgia FC.

207
00:09:43,350 --> 00:09:45,984
Son, I have a team of
top doctors from St. John's

208
00:09:46,019 --> 00:09:47,219
who take care of my players.

209
00:09:47,254 --> 00:09:49,465
I don't know who you are
or why you were on my field.

210
00:09:49,489 --> 00:09:52,457
Why exactly did you poach
a patient from St. John's

211
00:09:52,492 --> 00:09:54,837
- and bring him here?
- That's not what happened.
- I don't care.

212
00:09:54,861 --> 00:09:58,964
- I want Dax transferred
to St. John's immediately.
- Well, that would be a bad idea.

213
00:09:58,999 --> 00:10:02,383
Dax has sustained
significant injuries to his chest

214
00:10:02,418 --> 00:10:04,802
and his abdomen, leading
to multiple broken ribs,

215
00:10:04,838 --> 00:10:07,388
lung contusions,
lacerations to his spleen.

216
00:10:07,423 --> 00:10:09,307
I trust that, when
he stabilizes,

217
00:10:09,342 --> 00:10:12,337
- you'll make that transfer
happen as soon as possible.
- Y-You have my word.

218
00:10:12,361 --> 00:10:15,313
And I apologize for the
inconvenience. I-I hope...

219
00:10:20,203 --> 00:10:22,604
Bill Landry is the
richest man in Georgia,

220
00:10:22,639 --> 00:10:25,623
and in one morning you have
him pissed off at Chastain.

221
00:10:25,658 --> 00:10:28,693
You shouldn't have been anywhere
near Dax Ramsey to begin with.

222
00:10:28,728 --> 00:10:30,640
He asked for a second
opinion, so I helped.

223
00:10:30,664 --> 00:10:34,632
He's at Chastain now, so your
services are no longer required.

224
00:10:34,668 --> 00:10:35,834
Treating a patient

225
00:10:35,869 --> 00:10:38,285
without hospital privileges
is against the law.

226
00:10:38,338 --> 00:10:40,204
I'm not treating him.

227
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,372
I'm here as a friend.

228
00:10:41,408 --> 00:10:44,876
Which gives Dr. Hawkins
every right to stay.

229
00:10:44,911 --> 00:10:47,629
If you so much as lay a
finger on Dax Ramsey,

230
00:10:47,664 --> 00:10:49,664
I'll have you thrown
out and sued.

231
00:11:05,365 --> 00:11:07,543
Wow. You guys already
boarding patients in the hallway?

232
00:11:07,567 --> 00:11:09,350
One of those days.

233
00:11:09,385 --> 00:11:11,820
- You here for my admit?
- First one of the day.

234
00:11:11,855 --> 00:11:15,206
Riley, this is Dr. Pravesh.
He's gonna do an assessment.

235
00:11:15,241 --> 00:11:17,219
Okay. Hey, can I do the thing?

236
00:11:17,243 --> 00:11:19,044
The floor is yours.

237
00:11:19,079 --> 00:11:21,379
Riley Jackson,
28-year-old female.

